# Task List Management

Guidlines for creating and managing task lists in markdown files to track project progress

## Task List Creation

1. Create task lists in a markdown file (in the project root):
  - Use `TASK.md` file
  - Include clear title and description of the task

2. Structure of the file with these sections:
  ```markdown
  # {Feature name}

  Brief description of the feature and its purpose.

  ## Task status

  - [ done ] Task 1
    - [ done ] Task 1 subtask 1
    - [ done ] Task 1 subtask 2
  - [ done ] Task 2 description
  - [ in progress ] Task 3
    - [ done ] Task 3 subtask 1
    - [ in progress ] Task 3 subtask 2
    - [ to do ] Task 3 subtask 3
  - [ to do ] Task 4
  - [ to do ] Task 5
    - [ to do ] Task 5 subtask 1
    - [ to do ] Task 5 subtask 2
  - [ to do ] Task 6

  ## Implementation plan

  Detailed description of how the feature will be implemented.

  List of tasks in implementation order and detailed description.
  1. Task 1 - detailed description of the task 1
    a. Task 1 subtask 1 - detailed description of the subtask 1
    b. Task 1 subtask 2 - detailed description of the subtask 2
  2. Task 2 - detailed description of the task 2
  3. Task 3 - detailed description of the task 3
    a. Task 3 subtask 1 - detailed description of the subtask 1
    b. Task 3 subtask 2 - detailed description of the subtask 2
    c. Task 3 subtask 3 - detailed description of the subtask 3
  4. Task 4 - detailed description of the task 4
  5. Task 5 - detailed description of the task 5
    a. Task 5 subtask 1 - detailed description of the subtask 1
    b. Task 5 subtask 2 - detailed description of the subtask 2
  6. Task 6 - detailed description of the task 6

  ## All relevant files

  List of files which gonna by added or updated.

  Task 1 subtask 1:
  +   {File1.extension} to add
  -   {File2.extension} to remove
  +/- {File3.extension} to update

  Task 1 subtask 2:
  +   {File1.extension} to add
  -   {File2.extension} to remove
  +/- {File3.extension} to update

  Task 2:
  +   {File1.extension} to add
  -   {File2.extension} to remove
  +/- {File3.extension} to update

  Task 3 subtask 1:
  +   {File1.extension} to add
  -   {File2.extension} to remove
  +/- {File3.extension} to update

  (etc.)
  ```

3. Whenever a task is finished or the scope changed because of the fail from the build step update the `TASK.md` file
